Alright, so I'm trying to understand how GPS devices and satellite technologies could be part of a global conspiracy to make people think the Earth is round. Hmm, where do I even start? I know that most people believe the Earth is round because of these technologies, but maybe there's more to it.

First, I should think about how GPS works. I know that GPS uses satellites to determine locations. But wait, if the Earth were flat, would GPS still work the same way? Maybe the satellites are positioned in a way that only makes sense if the Earth is round. But maybe the programmers have tricked the system to simulate a round Earth even if it's flat. That could be a possibility.

Then there's the idea of satellite images. We see pictures from space, but how do we know those aren't just faked? Maybe the satellites are actually close to the ground, but the images are manipulated to look like they're from high up. That would explain why we don't see the curvature of the Earth in the images.


